1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:01,363
Introduction to Docker

2
00:00:01,900 --> 00:00:07,812
Docker is a platform that allows developers to automate the deployment of applications inside lightweight

3
00:00:08,012 --> 00:00:09,075
portable containers

4
00:00:09,463 --> 00:00:12,200
These containers bundle together the application code

5
00:00:12,613 --> 00:00:13,387
libraries

6
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:14,650
and other dependencies

7
00:00:15,075 --> 00:00:19,637
making it easy to ensure that software runs consistently across different environments

8
00:00:20,038 --> 00:00:23,475
Docker containers can be run on any system that supports Docker

9
00:00:23,938 --> 00:00:28,637
whether on a developer's laptop or in a large-scale production environment on cloud infrastructure

